      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GUNZ (2) finished in the placings over 1100m at Bendigo before the spell. Resumes with two wins at the jumpouts under the saddle, and he will be naturally improved. The speedy galloper will use the inside gate, and a bold run is likely. WANTED ENUFF (10) was well fancied on debut and was not far off the mark, beaten 2.75 lengths over 1108m at Kyneton. It was a tough effort from a wide gate, and she draws handy today. Sure to measure right up. HEGELY (8) was in the market first up over 1000m at Bendigo and it was a solid effort. Led and went close this track/trip prior, and was close up at Kilmore and Bendigo before that. One of the best contenders. MEET ME AT THE BAR (4) debuts and has looked good at the jumpouts. Jumps from an inside gate and the betting will be key. IMMORTAL TRUTH (9) is an improver from the Hayes yard and has to be kept onside.",
